                    "reference": {
                      "code": "YF",
                      "number": null,
                      "volume": "30",
                      "part": null,
                      "issue": null,
                      "page": "1553"
                    },
                    "date": 1979
                  }
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The value of the",
                "inelastic cross section of the 12-C+P reaction was",
                "taken as 250 +/- 2 mb."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-By authors.  In this case all the nuclei produced by",
                "beam fragmentation are emitted in a narrow cone along",
                "the beam direction and their momenta per nucleon are",
                "close to the projectile value.  Therefore, it is",
                "possible to detect all the nuclei that are produced,",
                "including those with very small energy in the",
                "projectile reference frame."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "SYNCY"
                ],
                "institute": "4ZZZDUB"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Slow extraction beam VP-1"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The ANOMALON magnetic spectrometer is based on a",
                "system of multiwire proportional chambers (MWPC) and an",
                "analysing magnet.  It also includes a Cherenkov",
                "hodoscope for determining fragment charges, a trigger",
                "system consisting of scintillation and Cherenkov",
                "detectors, and a beam monitor.  For the beam",
                "fragmentation cross section measurements the ANOMALON",
                "set-up was equipped with a liquid hydrogen target.",
                " MWPCs constitute a coordinate detector for determining",
                "The positions of the charged-particle tracks.",
                "More detailed description see:",
                "1. A.V.Zarubim et al., JINR B1-1-93-444 (1993)",
                "2. Yu.T.Borzunov et al., JINR Rapid Commun. 1/81 (1997)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target is 59 mm in diameter and 136 mm long",
                " (equivalent to 0.94 g/cm**2).  The total thickness of",
                "the two mylar windows is 67 mg/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
